Subject: [DSECRG-11-036] SAP NetWaver Virus Scan Interface - multiple XSS

[DSECRG-11-036] SAP NetWaver Virus Scan Interface - multiple XSS

SAP Netweaver Virus Scan Interface has linked XSS vulnerabilities. 

Application:     SAP NetWeaver 
Versions Affected:       SAP NetWeaver 
Vendor URL:      http://www.SAP.com
Bugs:    XSS
Reported:        01.04.2010
Vendor response:         08.04.2010
Date of Public Advisory:        11.11.2011
CVSS:    4.3
CVE-number: 
Author:  Dmitriy Evdokimov from DSecRG (research center of ERPScan)

Description
***********
SAP Netweaver Virus Scan Interface has linked XSS vulnerabilities.
Details
*******
1. XSS in VsiTestScan
Vulnerable servlet: VsiTestScan
Vulnerable parameters: instname
2. XSS in VsiTestServlet
Vulnerable servlet: VsiTestServlet
Vulnerable parameters: name

Example:
******
Working exploit is available in commercial scanner ERPScan Security Scanner for SAP (http://erpscan.com)

References
**********
http://erpscan.com/advisories/dsecrg-11-036-sap-netwaver-virus-scan-interface-multiple-xss/
http://www.sdn.sap.com/irj/sdn/index?rid=/webcontent/uuid/c05604f6-4eb3-2d10-eea7-ceb666083a6a
https://service.sap.com/sap/support/notes/1546307



Fix Information
*************
Solution to this issue is given in the SAP Security Note 1546307.


About DSecRG
*******
The main mission of DSecRG is to conduct researches of business critical systems such as ERP, CRM, SRM, BI, SCADA, banking software and others. The result of this work is then integrates in ERPScan Security Scanner. Being on the top edge of ERP and SAP security DSecRG research helps to improve a quality of ERPScan consulting services and protects you from the latest threads. 
Contact: research [at] dsecrg [dot] com
